                        <p style="marign-bottom:1px !importent">
                       <strong>Relational Database Concepts:</strong> 
                           <ul  style="list-style-type: none;">
                              <li style="padding-left:25px"> ->  DBMS basics</li>
                              <li style="padding-left:25px">-> Tables</li>
                              <li style="padding-left:25px">-> Schemas</li>
                              <li style="padding-left:25px">-> Primary & foreign keys</li>
                              <li style="padding-left:25px">-> Data normalization</li>
                              <li style="padding-left:25px">-> Abstraction</li>
                              <li style="padding-left:25px">-> Polymorphism</li>
                              
                           </ul>
                        </p>
                        <p style="marign-bottom:1px !importent">
                       <strong>SQL Fundamentals:</strong> 
                           <ul  style="list-style-type: none;">
                              <li style="padding-left:25px"> -> SELECT statements</li>
                              <li style="padding-left:25px">-> Filtering data</li>
                              <li style="padding-left:25px">-> Using WHERE clause</li>
                              <li style="padding-left:25px">-> JOIN operations (INNER, LEFT, RIGHT)</li>
                              
                              
                           </ul>
                        </p>
                        <p style="marign-bottom:1px !importent">
                       <strong>Data Manipulation Language (DML):</strong> 
                           <ul  style="list-style-type: none;">
                              <li style="padding-left:25px"> -> INSERT</li>
                              <li style="padding-left:25px">-> UPDATE</li>
                              <li style="padding-left:25px">-> DELETE statements for modifying data in tables</li>
                             
                           </ul>
                        </p>
                        <p style="marign-bottom:1px !importent">
                       <strong>Advanced Queries:</strong> 
                           <ul  style="list-style-type: none;">
                              <li style="padding-left:25px"> -> GROUP BY</li>
                              <li style="padding-left:25px">-> ORDER BY clauses</li>
                              <li style="padding-left:25px">-> Subqueries</li>
                              <li style="padding-left:25px">-> functions (aggregation, window)</li>
                              
                             
                           </ul>
                        </p>
                        <p style="marign-bottom:1px !importent">
                       <strong>Data Analysis with SQL:</strong> 
                           <ul  style="list-style-type: none;">
                              <li style="padding-left:25px"> -> Extracting insights</li>
                              <li style="padding-left:25px">-> summarizing data using aggregate functions</li>
                              
                           </ul>
                        </p>
                       
                        <p>
                       <strong>Introduction to SQL for Data Science:</strong>   Interacting with databases using Python libraries (e.g., SQLAlchemy).
